Tokens: Smallest unit of program.
Identifiers: Name of class, variables, methods, etc.
In java we have some rules for naming.
1. Allowed characters: a-z, A-Z, 0-9, and two special characters ($ and _).
2. We cannot start any name with numeric digit. (Example: 1a, 4d, etc)
3. Case sensitive. (name, Name both are different)
4. Length limit of characters. (In java we can give name as long we want but more than 15 character are not recommended)
5. We cant use name of reserved words.(which are 53 in java)
6. We can use the name of predefined classes and Identifiers.

Reserved words(53): further divided into 50 keywords & 3 constant literals.
constant literals: true,false,null
50 keywords: 48 used keywords, 2 unused.
2 unused: goto & const
48 used keywords: Data types(8), Access modifiers(11), Control statements(11), Exception handling(6), Object related(4), Class related(6)
Data types(8): byte, short, int, long, float, double, character, boolean
Access modifiers(11): public, private, protected, final, abstract, static, strictfp(1.2v), synchronized, native, transient, volatile
Control statements(11): if, else, for, do, while, switch, case, break, continue, default, return
Exception handling(6): try, catch, throw, throws, finally, assert(1.4v)
Object related(4): new, instanceof, super, this
Class related(6): class, import, package, implements, extends, interface
(void & enum(1.5v)): These two doesn't belogs to any cattegory.

