Types of variables on the basis of position in a class-
1. Instance/object-level/non-static variables: Values of these type of variables varies from object to object.
 By default value(0) provided by JVM, loads into the memory at the time of object creation, load in heap area, accessible by using reference variable only.
Declare inside the class but outside all the blocks without static keyword. Lifecycle(Instance var) = Lifecycle(Object) 
public class First {
